00:02:50.770 --> 00:02:56.140
Next up, it's Carissa Explains It All.

00:02:56.140 --> 00:03:00.700
Weird how there's always someone you think is the coolest.

00:03:00.700 --> 00:03:02.700
And you can't wait to be their best friend.

00:03:02.700 --> 00:03:05.700
And then, one day, there's a last person on Earth

00:03:05.700 --> 00:03:06.700
you want to be friends with.

00:03:06.700 --> 00:03:08.700
Well, that's exactly what happened to me

00:03:08.700 --> 00:03:10.700
with Betsy Dillweather.

00:03:10.700 --> 00:03:11.700
When we were freshmen,

00:03:11.700 --> 00:03:14.700
she seemed to be the coolest thing since Doc Martins.

00:03:14.700 --> 00:03:17.700
Then we all discovered Betsy's little secrets.

00:03:18.700 --> 00:03:23.140
Or take Cody Fern hotter.

00:03:23.140 --> 00:03:25.140
Nobody could touch him.

00:03:25.140 --> 00:03:27.140
He made Jason Priestley look like a dweeb.

00:03:27.140 --> 00:03:32.090
But by the time we were seniors,

00:03:32.090 --> 00:03:34.090
we discovered he had a kind of Dr. Jekyll

00:03:34.090 --> 00:03:36.090
and Mr. Hyde thing going on.

00:03:36.090 --> 00:03:42.480
That other strange thing that happens.

00:03:42.480 --> 00:03:45.480
One day, you're playing jacks and wearing a ponytail.

00:03:45.480 --> 00:03:47.480
And then you grow up.

00:03:47.480 --> 00:03:48.480
And the next thing you know,

00:03:48.480 --> 00:03:50.480
you're interested in a few other things.

00:03:50.480 --> 00:03:54.820
Which brings me to this weird thing

00:03:54.820 --> 00:03:56.820
about the time-space continuum.

00:03:56.820 --> 00:03:58.820
Have you ever noticed how it doesn't just move along

00:03:58.820 --> 00:04:00.820
in a continuous continuum?

00:04:00.820 --> 00:04:02.820
Instead, it hiccups along.

00:04:02.820 --> 00:04:03.820
And at certain moments,

00:04:03.820 --> 00:04:05.820
suddenly it feels like time's passed

00:04:05.820 --> 00:04:07.820
and you're at a whole new phase of your existence.

00:04:07.820 --> 00:04:09.820
Well, get ready for a big hiccup.

00:04:09.820 --> 00:04:12.820
Something I've been waiting for all my life.

00:04:12.820 --> 00:05:09.900
The end of high school as we know it.

00:05:09.900 --> 00:05:11.900
I just handed in my third feature to the dispatch

00:05:11.900 --> 00:05:13.900
about the mall scene and teen problems.

00:05:13.900 --> 00:05:16.900
Who would have thought I'd become a chronicler of teen life?

00:05:16.900 --> 00:05:18.900
Anyway, my editor even said he'd submit it

00:05:18.900 --> 00:05:19.900
for some kind of prize.

00:05:19.900 --> 00:05:21.900
But I just really like investigating what's going on

00:05:21.900 --> 00:05:23.900
and trying to get an idea of what might happen.

00:05:23.900 --> 00:05:27.900
So, from my last and final issue of the Thomas Tupper Times,

00:05:27.900 --> 00:05:30.900
I've decided to devote the whole issue to the future.

00:05:30.900 --> 00:05:33.900
I mean, where will we all be 20 years from now?

00:05:33.900 --> 00:05:35.900
Got me thinking about my friends and family.

00:05:35.900 --> 00:05:38.900
Like, I wonder where they'll be in 20 years.

00:05:38.900 --> 00:05:42.900
The year is 2014 and the future is now.

00:05:42.900 --> 00:05:44.900
Architect Marshall Darling,

00:05:44.900 --> 00:05:46.900
commissioned by President Chelsea Clinton,

00:05:46.900 --> 00:05:49.900
has redesigned the White House in the shape of an apple pie.

00:05:49.900 --> 00:05:54.690
After Janet Darling published her best-selling cookbook,

00:05:54.690 --> 00:05:56.690
One Thousand and One Ways to Enjoy Tofu,

00:05:56.690 --> 00:05:58.690
she moved to the last remaining rainforest

00:05:58.690 --> 00:06:01.690
to research her next book, Juices of the Jungle.

00:06:01.690 --> 00:06:05.960
And after being convicted of fraud

00:06:05.960 --> 00:06:08.960
in the Green Stamp scandal of 2011,

00:06:08.960 --> 00:06:10.960
Ferguson Darling had a spiritual awakening

00:06:10.960 --> 00:06:13.960
and went on to found the Church of Burgontology.

00:06:13.960 --> 00:06:14.960
Yes, come on!

00:06:14.960 --> 00:06:15.960
Give it to me!

00:06:15.960 --> 00:06:16.960
Yes!

00:06:16.960 --> 00:06:17.960
Yes!

00:06:17.960 --> 00:06:18.960
Come on!

00:06:18.960 --> 00:06:19.960
And me?

00:06:19.960 --> 00:06:22.960
Well, the good news is my future's all mapped out.

00:06:22.960 --> 00:06:24.960
I'm on my way to the College of Cincinnati

00:06:24.960 --> 00:06:26.960
School of Journalism.

00:06:26.960 --> 00:06:29.960
Hey, Cincinnati should be fun, right?

00:06:29.960 --> 00:06:34.620
Hi, Sam.

00:06:34.620 --> 00:06:36.620
Hey, Clarissa.

00:06:36.620 --> 00:06:37.620
I got another letter.

00:06:37.620 --> 00:06:39.620
From one of the colleges you applied to?

00:06:39.620 --> 00:06:40.620
Yeah.

00:06:40.620 --> 00:06:41.620
Well, great.

00:06:41.620 --> 00:06:42.620
What did it say?

00:06:42.620 --> 00:06:43.620
I don't know.

00:06:43.620 --> 00:06:44.620
I was afraid to open it.

00:06:44.620 --> 00:06:45.620
Sam, you have to open it.

00:06:45.620 --> 00:06:47.620
But what if it's another rejection?

00:06:47.620 --> 00:06:48.620
I don't know if I can take it.

00:06:48.620 --> 00:06:50.620
Sam, nobody expects to get in everywhere.

00:06:50.620 --> 00:06:53.620
Clarissa, I've applied to 23 schools.

00:06:53.620 --> 00:06:55.620
And that's not counting Bibbington College in Maine.

00:06:55.620 --> 00:06:57.620
Why aren't you counting that one?

00:06:57.620 --> 00:06:58.620
It's a girl's school.

00:06:58.620 --> 00:06:59.620
I applied by mistake.

00:06:59.620 --> 00:07:00.620
Oh.

00:07:00.620 --> 00:07:02.620
So what's the tally so far?

00:07:02.620 --> 00:07:03.620
21 rejections.

00:07:03.620 --> 00:07:04.620
And if this one's a reject,

00:07:04.620 --> 00:07:06.620
the only one left is Acme School of Engineering.

00:07:06.620 --> 00:07:08.620
Well, Sam, we've got to open this one.

00:07:08.620 --> 00:07:11.620
I should have never let my dad help me with my applications.

00:07:11.620 --> 00:07:14.620
He kept trying to stress my athletic accomplishments.

00:07:14.620 --> 00:07:17.620
But Sam, you don't really have any athletic accomplishments.

00:07:17.620 --> 00:07:19.620
Exactly.

00:07:19.620 --> 00:07:22.620
So what kind of school is this, Hamster Shire?

00:07:22.620 --> 00:07:23.620
It's brand new.

00:07:23.620 --> 00:07:25.620
They haven't even built the library yet.

00:07:25.620 --> 00:07:28.620
Their idea of education is totally avant-garde.

00:07:28.620 --> 00:07:30.620
Oh, you mean like no books, no term papers?

00:07:30.620 --> 00:07:31.620
No.

00:07:31.620 --> 00:07:32.620
It's like total immersion.

00:07:32.620 --> 00:07:34.620
You set your own curriculum with your teachers.

00:07:34.620 --> 00:07:36.620
Well, sounds great.

00:07:36.620 --> 00:07:38.620
Open it.

00:07:38.620 --> 00:07:39.620
Okay.

00:07:39.620 --> 00:07:40.620
Here goes.

00:07:40.620 --> 00:07:47.290
Dear Samuel Anders,

00:07:47.290 --> 00:07:49.290
although we at Hamster Shire College

00:07:49.290 --> 00:07:51.290
consider ourselves a new and innovative college,

00:07:51.290 --> 00:07:54.290
we can find no new way of saying no.

00:07:54.290 --> 00:07:55.290
Sorry.

00:07:55.290 --> 00:07:57.290
Rejected by a college that doesn't even exist.

00:07:57.290 --> 00:07:58.290
This is too much.

00:07:58.290 --> 00:07:59.290
Sam, I'm sorry.

00:07:59.290 --> 00:08:00.290
Yeah.

00:08:00.290 --> 00:08:02.290
Well, I guess I'd better go check out the backs

00:08:02.290 --> 00:08:03.290
of my dad's matchbooks.

00:08:03.290 --> 00:08:05.290
Maybe I'll find a correspondence school

00:08:05.290 --> 00:08:06.290
that'll take me.

00:08:06.290 --> 00:08:08.290
Sam, you're just too original for them.

00:08:08.290 --> 00:08:09.290
They don't know what they're missing.

00:08:09.290 --> 00:08:10.290
Thanks.

00:08:10.290 --> 00:08:12.290
But right now, the shanties cool of beauty

00:08:12.290 --> 00:08:14.290
is sounding better and better.

00:08:14.290 --> 00:08:15.290
Bye, Clarissa.

00:08:15.290 --> 00:08:16.290
See you, Sam.

00:08:16.290 --> 00:08:21.650
Well, Abraham Lincoln didn't go to college

00:08:21.650 --> 00:08:23.650
and it didn't hurt him.

00:08:23.650 --> 00:08:26.650
One way or the other, I'm sure Sam's going to land on his feet.

00:08:26.650 --> 00:08:27.650
I hope.

00:08:27.650 --> 00:08:31.790
Better get going on this last issue

00:08:31.790 --> 00:08:32.790
of the Thomas Tupper Times.

00:08:32.790 --> 00:08:35.790
I'm including a section on predictions for the future.

00:08:35.790 --> 00:08:36.790
Here's a question.

00:08:36.790 --> 00:08:39.790
What will it be like to drive in the information highway?

00:08:39.790 --> 00:08:42.790
If you get hungry, will there be a Stuckies?

00:08:42.790 --> 00:08:44.790
I wonder if you find yourself in virtual reality

00:08:44.790 --> 00:08:46.790
and you need to go to the bathroom.

00:08:46.790 --> 00:08:48.790
Oh, hello, sis.

00:08:48.790 --> 00:08:50.790
Why don't you look nice today?

00:08:50.790 --> 00:08:51.790
Ferguson, I'm busy.

00:08:51.790 --> 00:08:52.790
Out, leave, go. Goodbye.

00:08:52.790 --> 00:08:53.790
One minute, sis.

00:08:53.790 --> 00:08:55.790
Um, why don't you start with the window?

00:08:55.790 --> 00:08:58.790
Something more early American just might be the ticket.

00:08:58.790 --> 00:08:59.790
Uh, hi there.

00:08:59.790 --> 00:09:00.790
Hello.

00:09:00.790 --> 00:09:02.790
Oh, Clarissa, pardon me.

00:09:02.790 --> 00:09:04.790
Clarissa, I'd like you to meet Dudley, Dudley.

00:09:04.790 --> 00:09:05.790
Clarissa, my sister.

00:09:05.790 --> 00:09:06.790
Nice to meet you.

00:09:06.790 --> 00:09:07.790
Pleasure.

00:09:07.790 --> 00:09:09.790
Ferguson, what is Dudley doing in my room?

00:09:09.790 --> 00:09:11.790
Sis, I want you to congratulate you

00:09:11.790 --> 00:09:13.790
on your decision to matriculate

00:09:13.790 --> 00:09:15.790
at the College of Cincinnati School of Journalism,

00:09:15.790 --> 00:09:17.790
a fine institution.

00:09:17.790 --> 00:09:19.790
Although I wouldn't call Cincinnati

00:09:19.790 --> 00:09:21.790
one of the hottest college towns in the world,

00:09:21.790 --> 00:09:23.790
you do have Marge shot in the reds.

00:09:23.790 --> 00:09:25.790
Ferguson, that's enough.

00:09:25.790 --> 00:09:27.790
Get Dudley out of here before I do it.

00:09:27.790 --> 00:09:29.790
Okay, sis, let's cut to the chase.

00:09:29.790 --> 00:09:31.790
Uh, you're leaving and I'm staying.

00:09:31.790 --> 00:09:33.790
And as they say to the victor, it goes to the spoils.

00:09:33.790 --> 00:09:35.790
Namely, your room.

00:09:35.790 --> 00:09:36.790
Ferguson, you already have a room.

00:09:36.790 --> 00:09:38.790
Yes, but now I have an annex.

00:09:38.790 --> 00:09:39.790
Hey, that's my wall.

00:09:39.790 --> 00:09:41.790
Quick, Dudley, they're right on test.

00:09:41.790 --> 00:09:43.790
The only hazardous material in this room is you.

00:09:43.790 --> 00:09:44.790
Now get out.

00:09:44.790 --> 00:09:46.790
Oh, come on, Dudley.

00:09:46.790 --> 00:09:48.790
The barbarians never understand you.

00:09:48.790 --> 00:09:50.790
But what about the skylight measurements?

00:09:50.790 --> 00:09:51.790
Wow.

00:09:51.790 --> 00:09:56.350
My room and enemy hands.

00:09:56.350 --> 00:09:58.350
Now I know how the Romans felt when Attila the Hun

00:09:58.350 --> 00:09:59.350
was at the gates.

00:09:59.350 --> 00:10:00.350
Hi, Mom.

00:10:00.350 --> 00:10:01.350
That smells great.

00:10:01.350 --> 00:10:08.540
Here, taste.

00:10:08.540 --> 00:10:11.540
Mmm, it's really good.

00:10:11.540 --> 00:10:13.540
Not quite rich enough, right?

00:10:13.540 --> 00:10:14.540
Oh.

00:10:14.540 --> 00:10:16.540
I guess a bernet sauce with pureed tofu

00:10:16.540 --> 00:10:18.540
instead of all that egg yolk and butter

00:10:18.540 --> 00:10:19.540
doesn't quite work.

00:10:19.540 --> 00:10:21.540
I love French cuisine,

00:10:21.540 --> 00:10:23.540
but these recipes are also loaded with cholesterol.

00:10:23.540 --> 00:10:25.540
Here, Mom.

00:10:25.540 --> 00:10:27.540
I think just a touch of real butter

00:10:27.540 --> 00:10:28.540
should do the trick.

00:10:28.540 --> 00:10:30.540
Teresa, there must be a healthy

00:10:30.540 --> 00:10:32.540
substitute I can find.

00:10:32.540 --> 00:10:34.540
You know, Mom, after all these years,

00:10:34.540 --> 00:10:36.540
I think I'm really going to miss your special way

00:10:36.540 --> 00:10:38.540
with tofu when I go to college.

00:10:38.540 --> 00:10:40.540
Oh, come on, now I think that's one thing

00:10:40.540 --> 00:10:42.540
you won't mind saying goodbye to.

00:10:42.540 --> 00:10:44.540
College food will probably be the worst.

00:10:44.540 --> 00:10:46.540
I'll have to live on pizza and cheeseburgers

00:10:46.540 --> 00:10:48.540
and french fries day and night.

00:10:48.540 --> 00:10:50.540
Thank you, Manny.

00:10:50.540 --> 00:10:52.540
But the important thing is that everything's set.

00:10:52.540 --> 00:10:54.540
My future is clear.

00:10:54.540 --> 00:10:56.540
College will be great.

00:10:56.540 --> 00:10:58.540
Yeah, and you're going to one of the best journalism schools

00:10:58.540 --> 00:10:59.540
in the country.

00:10:59.540 --> 00:11:02.540
Can't wait to take my first journalism class.

00:11:02.540 --> 00:11:04.540
And Cincinnati should be fun.

00:11:04.540 --> 00:11:06.540
It's a great city, right?

00:11:06.540 --> 00:11:08.540
Yeah, there's lots to do in Cincinnati.

00:11:08.540 --> 00:11:10.540
Yeah.

00:11:10.540 --> 00:11:11.540
Like what?

00:11:11.540 --> 00:11:16.190
I'm sure you'll find something.

00:11:16.190 --> 00:11:18.190
You'll have a great time there.

00:11:18.190 --> 00:11:21.180
Who that could be?

00:11:21.180 --> 00:11:23.180
Maybe it's the French culinary police.

00:11:23.180 --> 00:11:24.180
I better get it.

00:11:24.180 --> 00:11:40.650
I just had to come over and tell you right away.

00:11:40.650 --> 00:11:42.650
Isn't this exciting?

00:11:42.650 --> 00:11:44.650
You won.

00:11:44.650 --> 00:11:45.650
I won? I won.

00:11:45.650 --> 00:11:46.650
What did I win?

00:11:46.650 --> 00:11:50.650
Your feature on malls and teen angst at one first place.

00:11:50.650 --> 00:11:52.650
That's incredible.

00:11:52.650 --> 00:11:54.650
So do I get like a trophy or something

00:11:54.650 --> 00:11:56.650
or maybe a plaque and a savings bond?

00:11:56.650 --> 00:11:58.650
Carissa, I thought you knew.

00:11:58.650 --> 00:11:59.650
Knew what?

00:11:59.650 --> 00:12:01.650
Who sponsored the contest.

00:12:01.650 --> 00:12:05.650
I submitted your feature to the Daily Post.

00:12:05.650 --> 00:12:07.650
The New York Daily Post?

