Am I a viking?

00:46:35.280 --> 00:46:36.280
Let me guess.

00:46:36.280 --> 00:46:39.970
A force field, right?

00:46:39.970 --> 00:46:41.970
No, just chicken.

00:46:42.970 --> 00:46:43.970
Fair enough.

00:46:43.970 --> 00:46:45.970
See you later.

00:46:46.970 --> 00:46:48.970
When we're on a lunch box.

00:46:49.970 --> 00:46:52.970
And then there were four.

00:46:52.970 --> 00:47:00.220
Five if you count Petunia.

00:47:00.220 --> 00:47:02.220
It's just a pay phone, sir.

00:47:02.220 --> 00:47:04.220
Circuits, metal and plastic.

00:47:04.220 --> 00:47:06.220
Why do you want to shoot it with a harpoon gun?

00:47:06.220 --> 00:47:09.220
I wanted to be a good volunteer,

00:47:09.220 --> 00:47:11.220
but I had to find out who the phone call was for.

00:47:11.220 --> 00:47:14.220
So I could lift the curse forever.

00:47:14.220 --> 00:47:17.220
Hello, and thanks for calling the ringing phone hotline.

00:47:17.220 --> 00:47:20.220
I wonder if you'd help us with a little questionnaire.

00:47:20.220 --> 00:47:21.220
Question one.

00:47:21.220 --> 00:47:23.220
It was you, wasn't it?

00:47:23.220 --> 00:47:25.220
You're the one who didn't answer the phone.

00:47:25.220 --> 00:47:26.220
Confess!

00:47:26.220 --> 00:47:33.890
We're here to help people, not brighten them.

00:47:33.890 --> 00:47:35.890
I am trying to help.

00:47:35.890 --> 00:47:37.890
I'll tell you what.

00:47:37.890 --> 00:47:39.890
Why don't you take a lunch break?

00:47:39.890 --> 00:47:41.890
It's your first day here.

00:47:41.890 --> 00:47:42.890
Take it easy.

00:47:42.890 --> 00:47:44.890
I'm hot. I'm on to something.

00:47:44.890 --> 00:47:46.890
Lunch break.

00:47:47.890 --> 00:47:49.890
I had to stop the curse.

00:47:49.890 --> 00:47:54.890
A curse that left its brand of madness on everyone it touched.

00:47:54.890 --> 00:48:00.230
Pete and his friends tried to keep their spirits up,

00:48:00.230 --> 00:48:05.230
but the combination of heat and fear is beginning to take its toll.

00:48:05.230 --> 00:48:38.440
As for me, I was there.

00:48:38.440 --> 00:48:41.440
Frustrated because I couldn't find the answers I was looking for.

00:48:41.440 --> 00:48:43.440
I tried to keep my cool,

00:48:43.440 --> 00:48:46.440
but the ringing phone was mocking me.

00:48:46.440 --> 00:48:48.440
Who have you come for?

00:48:48.440 --> 00:48:49.440
Who?

00:48:49.440 --> 00:48:51.440
Tell me!

00:48:51.440 --> 00:48:53.440
I'm not afraid of you!

00:48:53.440 --> 00:49:03.460
You should be.

00:49:03.460 --> 00:49:05.460
I know that voice.

00:49:05.460 --> 00:49:07.460
You call the hotline.

00:49:07.460 --> 00:49:09.460
What are you doing?

00:49:09.460 --> 00:49:10.460
Don't be alarmed.

00:49:10.460 --> 00:49:12.460
I'm a psychiatrist.

00:49:13.460 --> 00:49:15.460
A psychiatrist?

00:49:15.460 --> 00:49:17.460
Maybe you can help me.

00:49:17.460 --> 00:49:24.460
Meanwhile, one last obstacle stood in the way of the magnificent four.

00:49:24.460 --> 00:49:26.460
Out of our way, gatekeeper!

00:49:26.460 --> 00:49:27.460
Sorry, Chief.

00:49:27.460 --> 00:49:28.460
I can't let you cross.

00:49:28.460 --> 00:49:31.460
The street's been declared a danger area.

00:49:31.460 --> 00:49:33.460
I call it a stovetop.

00:49:33.460 --> 00:49:41.510
Asphalt to stop us!

00:49:41.510 --> 00:49:43.510
But Nona was wrong.

00:49:43.510 --> 00:49:48.510
In fact, it took nothing more than hot asphalt to stop them in their tracks.

00:49:48.510 --> 00:49:49.510
Freak!

00:49:49.510 --> 00:49:55.040
You'll have to go on without us!

00:49:55.040 --> 00:49:58.040
You can break the code of the crosswalk, Chief.

00:49:58.040 --> 00:50:00.040
But you can't break the laws of physics.

00:50:00.040 --> 00:50:02.040
That's what you think, crossboy?

00:50:02.040 --> 00:50:36.100
That's it!

00:50:36.100 --> 00:50:37.100
Problem!

00:50:37.100 --> 00:50:38.100
Rub!

00:50:38.100 --> 00:50:39.100
Let him!

00:50:39.100 --> 00:50:40.100
Hey, smart guys!

00:50:40.100 --> 00:50:42.100
What do you got to say for yourself now?

00:50:42.100 --> 00:50:44.100
Ah!

00:50:44.100 --> 00:50:45.100
It's over.

00:50:45.100 --> 00:50:47.100
Come put!

00:50:47.100 --> 00:50:49.100
Get a curcio!

00:50:49.100 --> 00:50:51.100
At least we tried to save the town.

00:50:51.100 --> 00:50:53.100
Yeah.

00:50:53.100 --> 00:50:58.010
What do you want on your tombstone?

00:50:58.010 --> 00:51:00.010
Here lies Pete and Artie.

00:51:00.010 --> 00:51:02.010
They answered the call.

00:51:02.010 --> 00:51:03.010
Yeah!

00:51:03.010 --> 00:51:08.500
Ellen! Ellen!

00:51:08.500 --> 00:51:10.500
A psychiatrist.

00:51:10.500 --> 00:51:12.500
A Dr. Burt Looper.

00:51:12.500 --> 00:51:15.500
He drew up this whole psychiatric profile the first passerby.

00:51:15.500 --> 00:51:16.500
Listen, listen.

00:51:16.500 --> 00:51:19.500
Probably filled with guilt.

00:51:19.500 --> 00:51:22.500
Feels the need to help out.

00:51:22.500 --> 00:51:26.130
Maybe here.

00:51:26.130 --> 00:51:29.130
Disturbed by the sound of ringing phones.

00:51:29.130 --> 00:51:32.020
Wow.

00:51:32.020 --> 00:51:34.020
Who could it be?

00:51:34.020 --> 00:51:36.020
I was about to find out.

00:51:36.020 --> 00:51:38.020
Ringing phone crisis center.

00:51:38.020 --> 00:51:43.870
Hey son, call me back.

00:51:43.870 --> 00:51:50.870
And if this works, your mother will never have to worry about a phone ringing in this house again.

00:51:50.870 --> 00:51:52.870
Mom?

00:51:52.870 --> 00:52:05.140
Let it smell your fear!

00:52:05.140 --> 00:52:06.140
Too late.

00:52:06.140 --> 00:52:11.140
Finally, Pete and Artie had come face to face with their dreaded phone.

00:52:11.140 --> 00:52:13.140
Your kind never learns, does it?

00:52:13.140 --> 00:52:15.140
No, Artie, don't do it.

00:52:15.140 --> 00:52:17.140
Please, boy.

00:52:17.140 --> 00:52:19.140
Stand back!

00:52:19.140 --> 00:52:22.140
This phone is going down for I.M. Artie!

00:52:22.140 --> 00:52:24.140
Ha ha ha ha!

00:52:24.140 --> 00:52:39.080
Last strongest man!

00:52:39.080 --> 00:52:44.280
And then there was one.

00:52:44.280 --> 00:52:47.280
It's the last roundup, cowboy-ed.

00:52:47.280 --> 00:52:50.280
Time for all good doggies to mosey on to bed.

00:52:50.280 --> 00:52:53.280
You giddy up now?

00:52:53.280 --> 00:52:55.280
I know, Mom.

00:52:55.280 --> 00:52:56.280
No, what dear?

00:52:56.280 --> 00:52:58.280
It was you, wasn't it?

00:52:58.280 --> 00:53:00.280
The phone call.

00:53:00.280 --> 00:53:02.280
It was for you this whole time.

00:53:02.280 --> 00:53:04.280
Why didn't you answer it?

00:53:04.280 --> 00:53:08.280
Pete, I was younger than you.

00:53:08.280 --> 00:53:14.280
I was just walking by and it started ringing and I thought it might be for me.

00:53:14.280 --> 00:53:17.280
But I was afraid.

00:53:17.280 --> 00:53:19.280
For 27 years?

00:53:19.280 --> 00:53:22.280
Yeah, well, I volunteer every day.

00:53:22.280 --> 00:53:26.280
And I've done everything I possibly can to help.

00:53:26.280 --> 00:53:28.280
Except answer it.

00:53:28.280 --> 00:53:31.280
Oh, I'm sorry.

00:53:31.280 --> 00:53:33.280
Look, I gotta go.

00:53:33.280 --> 00:53:40.080
What's going on?

00:53:40.080 --> 00:53:42.080
Somebody's gonna answer the phone.

00:53:42.080 --> 00:53:43.080
Who?

00:53:43.080 --> 00:53:45.080
Your brother.

00:53:45.080 --> 00:53:54.250
Pete.

00:53:54.250 --> 00:53:56.250
It had all come down to this.

00:53:56.250 --> 00:53:59.250
Pete was as scared as he'd ever been.

00:53:59.250 --> 00:54:02.250
But as he felt the panic surge through his body,

00:54:02.250 --> 00:54:05.250
he finally understood the curse of the ringing phone.

00:54:05.250 --> 00:54:08.250
I'll get it.

00:54:08.250 --> 00:54:11.250
It wasn't about learning the moment of your death

00:54:11.250 --> 00:54:13.250
or liquefying your brains.

00:54:13.250 --> 00:54:15.250
The curse was living in fear.

00:54:15.250 --> 00:54:19.250
And that was something he couldn't live with anymore.

00:54:19.250 --> 00:54:25.250
Excuse me.

00:54:25.250 --> 00:54:28.500
Joyce, what are you doing?

00:54:28.500 --> 00:54:31.500
I should have done 27 years ago.

00:54:31.500 --> 00:54:34.520
Pete!

00:54:34.520 --> 00:55:05.630
Hello?

00:55:05.630 --> 00:55:12.580
It's for you.

00:55:12.580 --> 00:55:17.710
Hello?

00:55:17.710 --> 00:55:27.100
This is kind of personal.

00:55:27.100 --> 00:55:28.100
Would you mind?

00:55:28.100 --> 00:55:33.480
Uh-huh.

00:55:33.480 --> 00:55:48.410
Why don't we talk about it, okay?

00:55:48.410 --> 00:55:53.450
For 27 years,

00:55:53.450 --> 00:55:57.450
Hub Callister had been reaching out to my mom.

00:55:57.450 --> 00:56:00.450
27 years of waiting

00:56:00.450 --> 00:56:20.960
for one woman to answer his call.

00:56:20.960 --> 00:56:24.960
I've loved you since the 7th grade.

00:56:24.960 --> 00:56:31.000
I just couldn't bring myself to tell you in person.

00:56:31.000 --> 00:56:34.250
So I called you on the phone

00:56:34.250 --> 00:56:37.250
when we walked by one day.

00:56:37.250 --> 00:56:39.250
Hub.

00:56:39.250 --> 00:56:44.650
When you didn't answer,

00:56:44.650 --> 00:56:47.650
I just kept it ringing.

00:56:47.650 --> 00:56:52.120
I got this job to stay with it.

00:56:52.120 --> 00:56:57.520
I just hoped that someday

00:56:57.520 --> 00:57:03.230
you'd pick it up.

00:57:03.230 --> 00:57:06.890
Hub, I like you,

00:57:06.890 --> 00:57:17.080
but I love my husband.

00:57:17.080 --> 00:57:19.080
You understand, don't you?

00:57:19.080 --> 00:57:28.830
After nearly three decades of fear,

00:57:28.830 --> 00:57:36.600
the curse was finally over.

00:57:36.600 --> 00:57:38.600
But as we were about to learn,

00:57:38.600 --> 00:57:41.600
the legend of the ringing phone would never end.

00:57:41.600 --> 00:57:49.300
Hub knew that mom would never pick up the phone,

00:57:49.300 --> 00:57:51.300
but it didn't really matter.

00:57:51.300 --> 00:57:54.300
To him, the rings were like an eternal flame.

00:57:54.300 --> 00:57:58.300
He kept lit by simply staying on the line.

00:57:58.300 --> 00:58:00.300
To this day, when we hear the rings,

00:58:00.300 --> 00:58:02.300
it reminds us that true love,

00:58:02.300 --> 00:58:04.300
if it's really true,

00:58:04.300 --> 00:58:06.300
doesn't need an answer.

