there's no telling what might happen.

01:31:52.310 --> 01:31:56.290
Or where the destruction would end.

01:31:56.290 --> 01:32:00.130
Submitted for the approval of the Midnight Society.

01:32:00.130 --> 01:33:01.990
I call this story, The Tale of the Renegade Virus.

01:33:01.990 --> 01:33:04.590
Suzanne, you've been in there for 20 minutes.

01:33:04.590 --> 01:33:06.510
Come on, honey, it's getting late.

01:33:06.510 --> 01:33:09.360
I need a ride to school, Dad.

01:33:09.360 --> 01:33:12.320
What's wrong with the bus?

01:33:12.320 --> 01:33:20.420
Hey.

01:33:20.420 --> 01:33:21.320
Ugh.

01:33:26.320 --> 01:33:29.000
You're going to help me with my science project tonight?

01:33:29.000 --> 01:33:30.800
No room.

01:33:30.800 --> 01:33:34.140
You're the best.

01:33:34.180 --> 01:33:36.380
You need a lift to school, honey?

01:33:36.380 --> 01:33:38.100
What's wrong with his bike?

01:33:38.100 --> 01:33:39.860
He has a flat tire.

01:33:39.860 --> 01:33:40.460
I'm OK.

01:33:40.460 --> 01:33:42.220
I'll ride Evan's bike.

01:33:42.220 --> 01:33:43.940
What's Evan going to ride?

01:33:43.940 --> 01:33:45.740
See you, Dad.

01:33:45.740 --> 01:33:54.130
Push your bike.

01:33:54.130 --> 01:33:54.890
10 seconds left.

01:33:54.890 --> 01:33:55.930
Down by five.

01:33:55.930 --> 01:33:58.010
Evan goes long.

01:33:58.010 --> 01:34:01.020
Touchdown!

01:34:01.020 --> 01:34:27.920
Nice catch.

01:34:27.920 --> 01:34:29.520
Thanks a lot.

01:34:29.520 --> 01:34:32.080
Hey, payback for the egg you put in my sneaker yesterday.

01:34:32.080 --> 01:34:35.440
Well, at least I didn't make you late.

01:34:35.440 --> 01:34:37.720
What's the matter?

01:34:37.720 --> 01:34:41.360
You got your combo?

01:34:41.360 --> 01:34:42.920
I switched our locks.

01:34:42.920 --> 01:34:43.760
Cute.

01:34:43.760 --> 01:34:51.260
Real cute.

01:34:51.260 --> 01:34:53.780
Hi, Sonia.

01:34:53.780 --> 01:34:55.980
You going to the game on Saturday?

01:34:55.980 --> 01:34:57.300
Yeah.

01:34:57.300 --> 01:34:58.940
How about you?

01:34:58.940 --> 01:35:00.020
Yeah.

01:35:00.020 --> 01:35:03.380
I thought maybe we could.

01:35:03.380 --> 01:35:05.460
I'm going with Simon.

01:35:05.460 --> 01:35:07.140
Maybe we'll see you there.

01:35:07.140 --> 01:35:19.650
Yeah, maybe.

01:35:19.650 --> 01:35:21.330
I'm going with Simon.

01:35:21.330 --> 01:35:23.010
Simon this.

01:35:23.010 --> 01:35:24.890
Simon that.

01:35:24.890 --> 01:35:27.450
Simon's the best.

01:35:27.450 --> 01:35:35.400
Yeah, right.

01:35:35.400 --> 01:35:38.680
Mr. Lewis, would you mind giving more effort

01:35:38.680 --> 01:35:40.440
into being here on time?

01:35:40.440 --> 01:35:41.440
Yes, Mr. Smith.

01:35:41.440 --> 01:35:43.760
Yes, you would mind giving more effort?

01:35:43.760 --> 01:35:50.660
I mean, no, Mr. Smith.

01:35:50.660 --> 01:35:52.260
You like payback?

01:35:52.260 --> 01:35:53.700
Well, just wait, Mr. Everything.

01:35:53.700 --> 01:35:57.920
You're going to wish never.

01:35:57.920 --> 01:36:02.080
Is this something you'd like to share with the entire class?

01:36:02.080 --> 01:36:04.360
Maybe a little less talking and a little more

01:36:04.360 --> 01:36:28.270
paying attention.

01:36:28.310 --> 01:36:29.670
He's probably still ticked out.

01:36:29.670 --> 01:36:31.870
Simon, Simon, Simon, come on.

01:36:31.870 --> 01:36:32.870
He's finished.

01:36:32.870 --> 01:36:34.910
I'm sorry about this morning, man.

01:36:34.910 --> 01:36:36.150
I didn't mean to get you in trouble.

01:36:36.150 --> 01:36:36.550
Forget it.

01:36:36.550 --> 01:36:37.230
It's history.

01:36:37.230 --> 01:36:38.230
Poe's ready.

01:36:38.230 --> 01:36:38.830
Who?

01:36:38.830 --> 01:36:40.550
Mr. Poe, the science teacher.

01:36:40.550 --> 01:36:42.470
He's been working on a computer game for months.

01:36:42.470 --> 01:36:44.430
We've been bugging him to get the first crack at.

01:36:44.430 --> 01:36:46.150
Let's go.

01:36:46.150 --> 01:36:47.430
This is not mad at you.

01:36:47.430 --> 01:36:48.630
Yeah.

01:36:48.630 --> 01:36:56.370
Well, I'll see you tomorrow, OK?

01:36:56.370 --> 01:37:02.580
Mr. Poe.

01:37:02.580 --> 01:37:05.540
Sound activated alarm.

01:37:05.540 --> 01:37:09.500
You cannot be too careful.

01:37:09.500 --> 01:37:13.680
You can't be too careful.

01:37:13.680 --> 01:37:15.240
Industrial spies.

01:37:15.240 --> 01:37:18.680
My boys, you are about to have the game-playing experience

01:37:18.680 --> 01:37:20.120
of a lifetime.

01:37:20.120 --> 01:37:21.480
Who goes first?

01:37:21.480 --> 01:37:22.400
Simon, me.

01:37:22.400 --> 01:37:24.720
You're the computer genius.

01:37:24.720 --> 01:37:26.480
That's the beauty of this game.

01:37:26.480 --> 01:37:29.000
You don't need to know a thing about computers to play.

01:37:29.000 --> 01:37:30.160
Cool.

01:37:30.160 --> 01:37:32.320
Sit down.

01:37:32.320 --> 01:37:35.600
Make yourself comfortable.

01:37:35.600 --> 01:37:39.040
So how do I play?

01:37:39.040 --> 01:37:42.080
Are you familiar with virtual reality?

01:37:42.080 --> 01:37:42.840
Sort of.

01:37:42.840 --> 01:37:45.120
It's a computer simulation of reality.

01:37:45.120 --> 01:37:47.520
It makes you feel like you're really there.

01:37:47.520 --> 01:37:50.520
The technology is in its infancy,

01:37:50.520 --> 01:37:54.200
but the possibilities are endless.

01:37:54.200 --> 01:37:58.640
I've made a breakthrough that surpasses any known program.

01:37:58.640 --> 01:38:04.810
My friends, we are about to step into history.

01:38:04.810 --> 01:38:10.320
Mr. Poe, where are the controls?

01:38:10.320 --> 01:38:16.410
Right there, in your mind.

01:38:16.410 --> 01:38:19.610
It's almost like going into a deep dream

01:38:19.610 --> 01:38:25.350
where everything seems real.

01:38:25.350 --> 01:38:29.990
Your neuron impulses react with the microwave circuitry.

01:38:29.990 --> 01:38:33.110
And that creates a certain force of energy.

01:38:33.110 --> 01:38:45.880
You don't know what to do.

01:38:45.880 --> 01:38:51.520
Tell them I'll be right there.

01:38:51.520 --> 01:38:55.000
I'm reluctant to work with the government.

01:38:55.000 --> 01:39:01.390
Too much paperwork.

01:39:01.390 --> 01:39:05.590
Simon, what's your preference?

01:39:05.590 --> 01:39:09.640
Would you like to go on a voyage to Saturn,

01:39:09.640 --> 01:39:14.830
be a night of the round table, or visit the dinosaurs

01:39:14.830 --> 01:39:16.990
of the Mesozoic?

01:39:16.990 --> 01:39:22.650
Well, I think I'll go with the night of the round table.

01:39:22.650 --> 01:39:24.250
Done.

01:39:24.250 --> 01:39:27.130
Once I start you, Evan will monitor the game

01:39:27.130 --> 01:39:30.130
while I get that call.

01:39:30.130 --> 01:39:33.090
Now, sit back for once.

01:39:33.090 --> 01:39:37.250
And just imagine that it's a great morning.

01:39:37.250 --> 01:39:38.810
This is a morning.

01:39:38.810 --> 01:39:40.770
Call in red.

01:39:40.770 --> 01:39:52.070
There's no reason for that.

01:39:52.070 --> 01:39:54.730
Ready, Simon?

01:39:54.730 --> 01:39:57.000
Ready.

01:39:57.000 --> 01:40:20.720
Then prepare yourself to take a trip.

01:40:20.720 --> 01:40:22.920
It was all a dream.

01:40:22.920 --> 01:40:30.280
Too bad.

01:40:30.280 --> 01:40:36.310
How'd that happen?

01:40:36.310 --> 01:40:39.900
Morning.

01:40:39.900 --> 01:40:59.110
Hey, anybody up?

01:40:59.110 --> 01:41:00.310
Mom?

01:41:00.310 --> 01:41:04.240
Dad?

01:41:04.240 --> 01:41:05.040
What's going on?

01:41:05.040 --> 01:41:06.440
Have you seen Simon this morning?

01:41:06.440 --> 01:41:07.520
No.

01:41:07.520 --> 01:41:08.400
Funny.

01:41:08.440 --> 01:41:09.680
I wonder where he is.

01:41:09.680 --> 01:41:11.240
I'm right here.

01:41:11.240 --> 01:41:13.000
Susan, would you call your brother?

01:41:13.000 --> 01:41:24.600
Simon!

01:41:24.600 --> 01:41:25.880
Are you down there?

01:41:25.880 --> 01:41:32.760
I'm up here, Simon.

01:41:32.760 --> 01:41:35.050
Mom?

01:41:35.050 --> 01:41:36.130
Mom?

01:41:36.130 --> 01:41:52.180
I'm in here.

01:41:52.180 --> 01:42:05.340
Don't be late for school.

01:42:05.340 --> 01:42:20.440
Simon, could I have a word with you?

01:42:20.440 --> 01:42:23.420
Dad?

01:42:23.420 --> 01:42:26.100
Is Ron dreaming of something real strange that's going on?

01:42:26.100 --> 01:42:30.450
Well, son, you're not dreaming.

01:42:30.450 --> 01:42:39.220
I guess that leaves us with something strange.

01:42:39.220 --> 01:42:42.220
Stay tuned for more of the Big Help on SNCC.

